Class MainGUI

java.lang.Object
java.awt.Component
java.awt.Container
java.awt.Window
java.awt.Frame
javax.swing.JFrame
marketplace.GUI.MainGUI
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Runnable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants
public class MainGUI
extends javax.swing.JFrame
implements java.lang.Runnable
The MainGUI file is the initialiser for the gui for clients. It starts the GUI at the login page. Sets handlers and starts the main frame that all other gui panels are held in. This is the window that holds the program's GUI.
See Also:
for GUI files, Serialized Form
